# Keep Files Small

- Prefer small, focused files with one primary responsibility.
- Target size: keep files at or under 300 lines.
- Soft warning at 220+ lines: look for extraction opportunities before adding more.
- Hard limit at 350+ lines: split before adding new features unless explicitly requested.
- Extract repeated literals/config into lookup or util files.
- Extract reusable UI blocks into components and shared hooks.
- Avoid adding unrelated logic to an already large file.
- New features in large files should be implemented by creating adjacent modules first.

## Split Strategy

- Move pure helpers to `src/utils/*`.
- Move constants/lookups to `src/data/*` or `src/utils/*Lookups.ts`.
- Move view sections to `src/components/*`.
- Move stateful reusable logic to hooks.

## Example

```ts
// ❌ BAD: huge page file with helpers/constants/UI mixed together
```

```ts
// ✅ GOOD: page composes smaller modules from utils/components/hooks
```
